cs.CV, cs.NE, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CL 

The paper discusses convolutional networks, which are primarily used in computer vision tasks such as image classification, object detection, and segmentation. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also discusses the theoretical and biological bases of ConvNets, which suggests that it may also belong to cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper discusses attempts at understanding ConvNets through visualizations and empirical studies, which could place it in cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.CL (Computation and Language).
